meanings.definition: (historical) Sir William Gascoigne (c. 1350–1419), Chief Justice of England during the reign of King Henry IV.
meanings.english_definition: Sir William Gascoigne (c. 1350–1419), an English judge who served as Chief Justice of England during the reign of King Henry IV.

meanings.definition: A habitational surname from Gascony in France.
meanings.english_definition: A habitational surname, denoting someone originating from Gascony in France.

etymology.value: Derived from the region of Gascony in France.
